workouts.name: Threshold 90s + Tempo
workouts.description: A mixed interval + tempo workout that challenges you to sustain your speed on fatigued and tired legs. Focus on a steady but fast pace for the tempo effort.

workouts.name: Strength for Runners
workouts.description: A routine that includes mobility, single leg strength and can be done before or after an easy aerobic run.

workouts.name: 5 min Ramp Up
workouts.description:
This workout is designed to enhance your ability to sustain and surge past threshold pace, simulating race conditions and boosting your speed endurance.

Start each rep at a Threshold effort and increase the pace with 90 seconds to go. 

Save some energy for the final 90 seconds so you can really push the pace.

workouts.name: Aerobic Rollers
workouts.description:
Aerobic base building run. The goal is to keep a steady pace that feels relaxed and smooth.

Run on a rolling road or trail, with significant vert and try to push on the downhills while keeping HR low on uphills.

Breathing is conversational, but its not an easy run. This effort falls between easy and tempo. Steady.

workouts.name: Vert Heavy Trail Run
workouts.description:
Head out for a longer, steady-paced trail run. Focus on maintaining a consistent, comfortable effort throughout the run.

Aim for 3k+ feet of climbing on terrain that is similar or steeper than your goal race.

This run is key to building the stamina and strength you'll need for your upcoming trail race. Remember to bring hydration and fuel to keep your energy levels stable throughout.

workouts.name: Recovery Run
workouts.description:
Focus on active recovery! Keep the pace very slow and effort very low (3-5 RPE)

You should feel better after this run than when you started

workouts.name: Strides
workouts.description:
Easy aerobic effort with short strides at the end to turn the legs over.

Stay strictly in Z2 for the main run (RPE 4–5). Add 4–6 strides near the end — 20–30 seconds at quick, relaxed effort with full recovery. These aren’t sprints. Smooth, powerful, and under control.

workouts.name: Aerobic Maintenance
workouts.description:
Aerobic maintenance, to maintain aerobic gains without taxing the system. The goal is to keep a steady pace that feels relaxed and smooth.

Breathing is conversational, but its not an easy run. This effort falls between easy and tempo. Steady.

workouts.name: Race Sim + Gear Check
workouts.description:
This is your longest controlled nutrition rehearsal.

Goal: Have your race kit dialed in. Know what goes in what pocket. Where each bottle is going.

Treat this as a dress rehearsal: nutrition, gear, pacing, terrain — everything.

Early effort must stay boring and easy (RPE 3-4). This is not a speed day — it’s a gut training day. The final 90-120min may allow light progression if you’re handling fuel well.

Lay out your gear and fuel the day before.

Test fluid intake, sodium, gels, calories

Gear & pack should mirror race setup

Socks, Shoes, anti chafing, use all your race day gear. No exceptions.

workouts.name: Jumping + Posterior Chain
workouts.description:
Mixed strength workout hitting some fast twitch muscles and some heavier lifting.

Focused on legs, glutes and explosiveness.

workouts.name: Back-to-Back
workouts.description:
Head out for a longer, steady-paced trail run. Focus on maintaining a consistent, comfortable effort throughout the run.

No need to push pace, focus on fueling and positive mindset. Enjoy a low pressure day on the trails.. with tried legs.

This run is key to building the stamina and strength you'll need for your upcoming trail race. Remember to bring hydration and fuel to keep your energy levels stable throughout.

workouts.name: Explosiveness + Power
workouts.description:
Mixed strength workout hitting some fast twitch muscles and some heavier lifting.

Focused on legs, glutes and explosiveness.

workouts.name: Strength Day Shakeout
workouts.description: An easy shakeout before or after your mobility workout. Purpose is to loosen up the legs and get ready for your next big workout.

workouts.name: Mixed Intervals - 30s + 2min
workouts.description:
This mixed interval workout has some fast, interval effort on the front and tail end, with some steady threshold efforts in between.

This workout is intended to be run hard in the middle. The last set of 30 second reps is time to let loose.
